Tough Kenya’s hope of higher ranking goes up in smoke as country is relegated to Davis Cup Africa Zone Group ThreeBut Kenyan girls finished top in girls’ Under-14 and Under-16 categories in East Africa Championships to brighten gloomy year Tennis Kenya had one of the most successful years in 2019, highlighted by Kenya qualifying for the Euro/Africa Group 2 Davis Cup play-offs, but hopes of a replicating that feat in 2020 went up in smoke when tennis activities, like those of other sports, were suspended when coronavirus pandemic struck. 



