But Kenya's hope of featuring in the Euro/Africa Group Two tournament were shattered on March 7 after the team lost two decisive matches to Indonesia in the best of five Euro/Africa Group 2 play-off tournament at the Gelora Bung Karno Tennis Stadium in Jarkarta. 

Changawa beaten 

Kenyan duo of Ismael Changawa and Ibrahim Kibet lost in three straight sets 6-7, 7-6, 7-6 to Christopher Rungkat and David Susanto of Indonesia in the best-of-five doubles contest. 

Later, Kevin Cheruiyot lost 6-4, 6-2 to Trismuwantara Gunawan, signalling the team's relegation back to Davis Cup Africa Zone Group Three category. 






Kenya's provisional team for the Davis Cup Africa Zone Group III Tennis Championship (from left): Kevin Cheruiyot, Ibrahim Kibet, Petty Andanda, Ryan Randiek, Ismail Changawa and Olivier Kigotho train at the Nairobi Club on June 5, 2018.
Photo credit: Chris Omollo | Nation Media Group

 

Kenya last qualified for Euro/Africa Group Two tournament in 1992 when Paul Wekesa, Asif Karim, Nobert Oduor and Eno Polo represented the country. 

Kenya has paid dearly for her absence from 2015 Davis Cup qualifiers. It is at the tournament that the International Tennis Federation (ITF) introduced new rules for promotion of teams, specifically the use of four-year track performance to rank teams in different groups. Kenya dropped to Group Three. 






Six months after cancellation of all sporting activities in Kenya including tennis, the Ministry of Sports issued guidelines for the resumption of outdoor recreational non-contact sporting activities, including athletics, lawn tennis, golf, motorsport, cricket, cycling and badminton. 



